1. Download Jenkins war file from below site
#https://updates.jenkins-ci.org/download/war/

Keep above file in "C" or "D" drive
Open Command Prompt and reach to the jenkins war file

And run this command - "java -jar jenkins.war"

open browser and type "http://localhost:8080"

After account setup on jenkins
Login to jenkins
Click on New Items and find Maven Project

If Maven Project is not available, download from Manage Jenkins--> Manage Plugins

Repeat step 13
Enter Project name and select Maven and click on OK

Scroll down on page and click on the "tool configuration" in maven section

Add maven name there--> APPly & SAVE

ADD Pom.xml file location of your system

Make sure jdk in your project and in Jenkins should be same. JDK path can be setup by 

Use of maven compiler plugin-
	<plugin>
		<groupId>org.apache.maven.plugins</groupId>
		<artifactId>maven-compiler-plugin</artifactId>
		<version>3.8.1</version>
			<configuration>
				<source>${jdk.level}</source>
				<target>${jdk.level}</target>
			</configuration>
	 </plugin>
pass your textng.xml file in pom.xml file by surefire plugin
